> Part sweet, part tangy, and all-around delicious—that's the thick and super flavorful glaze drizzled all over these pork chops. The rich cherry and balsamic flavors balance each other out perfectly. So we've kept the sides simple with roasted green beans and couscous to allow the meat and sauce to shine. And boy, do they steal the show.

== Roasted Green Beans ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4 servings).

Toss @green beans{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Couscous ==

While green beans roast, melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} and half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings); cook, stirring, until toasted and fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4) and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Pork ==

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside.

== Cherry Balsamic Glaze ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add sliced onion; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}; simmer until slightly reduced, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @cherry jam{2%tablespoon} and ⅓ cup water (½ cup for 4 servings). Cook until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt, pepper, and up to ½ tsp @sugar{½%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4) to taste.

Turn off heat. Stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

Return pork to pan; turn to coat in sauce.

== To Serve ==

Fluff couscous with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Divide pork, couscous, and green beans between plates. Top pork with any remaining sauce and serve.